epresentations of reductive symmetric spaces. The book provides a general introduction to the theory of D-modules on flag varieties, and it describes spherical D-modules in terms of a cohomological formula. Using microlocalization of representations, the author derives a criterion for irreducibility. The relation between multiplicities and singularities is also discussed at length.Originally published in 1990.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aMATHEMATICS / Geometry / Non-Euclidean.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1980-1999z978311041344108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Sciencez978311041359508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Mathematical Notes eBook-Package 1970-2016z978311049492108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066592508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140086207840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400862078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400862078.jpg  a978-3-11-041344-1  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1980-1999c1980d1999  a978-3-